		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">Bregalad wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"> same brand new games were $40 in USA and even less in Japan.</div><br /><br />Japan games price have always been higher compared to the US. In general, unless it's a portable game, the average price is 7300 yen, which depending of the exchange rate at the time, can be between 70$~100$ US when the identical game would be 50$ in the US.  The only time it is cheaper these days if it's an American/European game sold in Japan, like &quot;The Last Of Us&quot; since foreign games don't sale well anyway.<br /><br />@Koitsu<br /><br />You can try to send something to Brazil but there is no guaranty that the person will receive it in the first place, i.e. post office seems quite, well, not that &quot;straight&quot;, if you know what I mean ... I have experience for a small package I sent once.

		

