		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">Banshaku wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">You can try to send something to Brazil but there is no guaranty that the person will receive it in the first place, i.e. post office seems quite, well, not that &quot;straight&quot;, if you know what I mean ... I have experience for a small package I sent once.</div><br />That's true... I haven't really detected a pattern yet... All Flash carts I got from Krikzz arrived safe and sound (and pretty quickly too!), but the Famicom cart Banshaku sent me just turned into smoke... Since then I also have lost a Game Boy Advance SP Brighter I got on Ebay (ended up buying a beaten up one from a brazilian seller, along with a new housing, which I have yet to replace). There was also a pack of 5 universal game cases that never arrived, but based on the tracking information things went bad for this package while it was still in the US.<br /><br />I don't know if people really steal these things... I mean, I can imagine someone grabbing my GBA for their nephew or something, but what would a regular person do with a Famicom cart nowadays? Most people probably don't even know what console they're supposed to put that cart in.

		

